DEVICE_FINISH_UP_FLAG - Static variable in class com.ihealth.communication.control.UpgradeProfile
The key of the upgrade result.
Value:
0 indicates upgrade failed. 1 indicates upgrade/transmit successfully. Note:
If the value is 1, if DEVICE_UP_MODE == 100, it indicates transmit successfully, device will upgrade itself. If the value is 1, if DEVICE_UP_MODE == 101, it indicates upgrade successfully. If the value is 1, device will disconnect automatically, need to discovery and connect again.

DEVICE_UP_ERROR - Static variable in class com.ihealth.communication.control.UpgradeProfile
The key of the error code of upgrade.
Value:
200 indicates network error. 201 indicates no call iHealthDevicesUpgradeManager.queryUpgradeInfoFromDeviceAndCloud(String, String) before iHealthDevicesUpgradeManager.startUpGrade(String, String) 300 indicates device connection error. 301 indicates device stop upgrade. 302 indicates invalid input parameters. 400 indicates no need to upgrade. 401 The AppSecret is wrong. 402 The info file not exist. 403 The crc is null. 404 The crc is wrong. 405 The model is wrong. 406 The firmware file is incomplete.

disconnect() - Method in interface com.ihealth.communication.control.DeviceControl
Disconnect device This is an asynchronous call, it will return immediately. If disconnect successfully, following callback will be triggered:
iHealthDevicesCallback.onDeviceConnectionStateChange(String mac, String deviceType, int status, int errorID)
The status will be 2(iHealthDevicesManager.DEVICE_STATE_DISCONNECTED). Attention, it is mandatory to call following method before you call this method:
iHealthDevicesManager.registerClientCallback(iHealthDevicesCallback)
